animal.description:
My name is CIABELLA and I'm a beautiful 2 yr F AmStaff/Pit X. I'm a petite 50 lbs of PURE SUGAR SWEETNESS. My owner passed away tragically and I'm on my own and temporarily staying with friends but their female dog is not accepting me so I have to leave! I'm very sweet, good with all people and I used to live with other dogs but they were all male so I seem to like male dogs more than female dogs.... but it would be best if I was a SOLO DOG. I like to chase cats too much so NO CATS for me and I've never been around young kids so older kids ages 10 yrs + would be best. I walk well on leash, know basic commands and am housebroken. I'm not fond of being crated but I'm not destructive when left alone. I'm young and medium active and still have alot to learn but I'm quick to learn and eager to please. I'm used to living in a home with a large fenced in yard so that would be ideal....but more importantly I need someone that has had previous experience with my breed that will know, understand and & appreciate me!! I'm an ABSOLUTE GEM that will SPARKLE in the right home!

For more info/application - please email: INFO@TAILSOFLOVERESCUE.ORG

animal.description:
She came to the shelter as a stray after being found by a customer down the road from AAP~ Poor little Sierra has had a rough life. She was brought in by a customer coming to adopt a cat after she was found wandering on the highway near the street the shelter is on. Sadly she looked really rough and in bad shape as she was severely malnourished and covered in dirt and fleas. She tested positive for heart worm and has gone through treatment which extended her stay at the shelter. We later discovered that she was previously used for breeding to supplement someone's income. Luckily for her she got away from that life and is now looking for a life of luxury, or at least a comfortable life with lots of love and attention. Despite being mistreated in the past, this sweet girl has nothing to give but LOVE. She loves treats, kisses and most of all cuddles. This sweet little girl is more than ready to go to her forever home to be treated like the princess that she is. She is good with other dogs and great with people. She is older now, more mature and laid back, and would prefer older children as young active children make her a little nervous. She will need some work and reinforcement on house rules and bathroom habits.  Sierra really needs an inside home with a securely fenced yard to play in with her family. She is spayed, vaccinated including rabies, wormed, was treated for heart worm, and micro-chipped. She, like every dog, needs to be on heart worm prevention for life. Come and meet our sweet Sierra!

Note:  To adopt, you must live within approximately 100 miles of one of our adoption sites (Benld, O'Fallon or Springfield IL), and be at least 18 years of age.

animal.description:
So sweet!Maria was born around December 1, 2012, and weighs about 20 pounds. Somehow Maria found herself sitting in a high kill shelter in Kentucky. The shelter reached out to us knowing we have a soft spot for older dogs and Joyful happily agreed to bring her to safety. Maria is one incredibly sweet girl! She is all wiggles and kisses when you greet her and just wants to spend time with her humans. Maria does wonderfully with the other dogs and we can't imagine her being an issue with children however with her older age perhaps not teeny tiny children who don't yet know how to be gentle with dogs. Maria appears to have luxating patellas on both hind legs. This is rather common in smaller breed dogs. There is a surgery that can repair the patellas but at Maria's age and seeing that she is not bothered by the condition we are choosing to not do the surgery. Please talk with your vet or do some research to make sure you are comfortable with this if you are thinking about adopting. Maria rode well in the car and walks nicely on a leash. We know you will love her as much as we do!
foster mom update!!! She is a joy to have around. Very happy and easy-going. Likes to lounge around with the family. Gets along just fine with all my dogs and cat. She is fully potty trained and has no issues with stairs. We are working on getting her weight down. She is just the sweetest little Chunky Monkey, as I call her.
The adoption Fee for this dog is $400.00 Adoptions fees vary based on adoptability.
In general, our fees include spay/neuter, all age-appropriate vaccines, Home Again microchipping & registration, worming & flea control - a 'complete' pet. We accept CASH or Visa/Mastercard ONLY. Joyful Rescues has no funding except for our adoption fees and miscellaneous donations. Pet care and vet bills are expensive - you must be ready to take on this financial (as well as emotional) responsibility. YOU MUST BE AT LEAST 25 YEARS OF AGE TO ADOPT A DOG FROM JOYFUL RESCUES We keep our pet list as up-to-date as possible. As soon as a pet is adopted, it is removed from the list. If a pet is still showing, it is still available for adoption. Can't Adopt Me? SPONSOR ME Look for the Link 'Special Instructions to Seller' if you want to note a particular pet
Before you seek to adopt a pet from Joyful Rescues, please read our Pet Adoption page http://www.joyfulrescues.org/pet_adoption.html.

Online Application

animal.description: Charli is quiet and kind. She will just look up and you and wag her tail to let you know she appreciates your help. She can also smile. She warms up to new dogs after a slow introduction. Charli has not been around cats, so we do not know how she would do. She is excellent on leash with a collar and/or harness. She doesn't pull and usually stays by your side. Charli has a low energy level, but we suspect it has more to do with decompressing and symptoms of heartworms. She has spurts of energy and playfulness and is excited to go on walks. But is mostly resting. Thus far we have not encountered too many things that scare her or make her uneasy. She was leery of the garage door, but just viewed it with caution. So far she has taken everything in stride. She is doing excellently with potty training. She goes when we take her out, takes advantage of walks, and has had no accidents in her crate. The past few nights she has slept in the foster's in-home office, out of the crate, and she has done great! We haven't given her the chance to really ask to go out, because we take her out every 2-3 hours. But I think she's smart and would figure it out quickly. Charli would do wonderfully in a quiet home with older kids that can give her the attention she deserves. We think she would be best as an only dog, but can get along with others as she shows no interest in playing with the foster's dog but vies for attention. She really loves people. If local and interested in fostering Charli through her heartworm treatment and then adopting her, please apply.

animal.description: Hi!! Thank you for checking out my bio. Where do I start? My dame is Dasher. I was found living under an abandon house with my babies right before Christmas. I have never known what a real home is like. I was out here on the streets fending for myself and then I had to protect my babies. This made it hard for me to trust people. On Dec 7th my babies and I were rescued!!! They found their forever homes but I needed more time to learn to trust people. My foster family came and picked me up and they have been wonderful to me. They give me time and space to learn what it is to be a part of a family. Everyday is getting easier and better. As much as I love my foster family I am looking for my forever family. Is that you? I need a family who is patient, kind and caring that will teach me I can trust them. If you feel you could give me that home please email foster@specialpals.org so we can set up a meeting. Thank you!!! P.S. I have a favorite blankie and stuffie that I need to bring with me. I hope you don't mind.

animal.description:
Layla here- just checking in. Wanted to let y’all know how I’m doing at my new pad.

I am feeling more and more at home each day. This family seems to really like having me around. There’s 2 kids to play with; a little boy and a little girl. It’s so much fun to run around with them in the backyard. We play tag, fetch and hide and seek. There are so many fun smells around... I’ve spotted/smelled at least 12 doggie friends that live right near me. I see them from the deck- sometimes we talk to each other- they all say this is a great place to live.

Mom and dad love having me around. I know how to make mom feel better- i snuggle right up to her and sometimes on top of her or dad. They say I am a great snuggler and call me a snuggle-buggle just like the human kids ? 

Speaking of snuggling- they let me sleep on the couch- wow!!! Sometimes, I get lonely so I go upstairs. The little girl loves having me sleep on her bed so I jump up sleep and then surprise her in the morning. Oh and the little boy, asks me to take naps with him. I’ve slept in every comfy spot in the house. 
 
I’ve been a good eater. No new  accidents in the house. I’m pretty good at letting mom and dad know when i need to go out. I do have some stinky toots but they seem to be getting better. 

The whole family has been helping me remember my training. I’m really good at sit, paw, drop it and down; still working on stay and wait- its just that i get so excited to be with my family its hard to stay, but they don’t give up on me. We’ve practiced a little on my leash and mom said I am doing well. I go in the crate when they ask me to. Once I learned that they come back home, I’ve been much better. I just miss them when they leave. 

Even though I’ve played with lots of doggy friends at dog daycare, I would really prefer to be the only pet in the home. I would adore having some tiny human siblings to do things with.

animal.description:
Sonny

My name is Sonny and I try hard to live up to my name even though I behave a little more like Eeyore instead. I had a sister who was with me most of my life and since we’ve gotten separated, I can be sad and grumpy because I miss her. I was very protective of her and so I sometimes have trouble around other dogs since I want to be the center of attention and receive the most petting. For this reason I will need to be an only dog.  

I also am not my happiest around young children who can sometimes be unpredictable and startle me.  I have snapped at children in the past and it is important that I go to a home that does not have children or grandchildren.  As far as adults go though, I love to be petted (ears and belly are my favorite), I love taking walks/hikes, and I’ll sit and cuddle during the evening. I’m 8 years old and am a very mellow guy, so
I’d be a great companion in a quiet, stable, and loving adult-only home. 

My foster parents think I was hit/kicked by a previous owner because I sometimes snap when startled and I have bitten when I’m started too.  They were not bad bites, but I just get so scared when something happens that I am not expecting.  Gentle redirection and assurance that everything is okay are the best ways to correct me, as I really want to please my humans.  I have been evaluated by a trainer, and there are notes and suggestions by the trainer to guide my new owner in the best way to work with me on my behavior, which is for the most part very good!  The trainer even said that I seem to get along with cats!  

My new owner will need to be committed to helping me work through my issues, and the rescue is willing to pay for a session with the trainer that I saw (Sol Dog) to get my adopter started on the right track. 

If you can deal with a little snoring at night, I am happy to be your new companion during this pandemic and forever!  My adoption fee is $225, and the rescue will pay for the visit with the trainer. 

This dog's adoption fee is a minimum $225.00 donation to help us save more dogs. Southern Arizona Beagle Rescue, SoAZBR is an all-volunteer group. One hundred percent of your donation is used for the care and treatment needy beagles. Your donation is 100% tax deductible, too.

We URGENTLY need fosters so we can help save more dogs.  If you can help, please contact us.

animal.description:
Say hello to our little friend, Colby Jack! CJ or Colby for short. This handsome boy is 15lbs of pure love who enjoys being carried and held. We'd classify him as an ambivert because he enjoys socializing at the dog park and recharges by gnawing on a bone in a corner or sleeping on the nearest blanket. He's very calm, quiet, and low energy. When inside, he will follow you around in hopes of getting in your lap or laying down next to you for a nap. He's house trained and crate trained! 

Don't be fooled by his tiny legs. This little guy loves his walks and will go for as long as you let him. He's never met a dog or human he doesn't like, whether kids or adults. He just loves being loved on, and who can resist his precious, bearded face?! 

He will do better when left alone in a crate before giving him free rein so he can get used to his surroundings and used to you coming and going. When encouraged and rewarded with treats (jerky or soft chews are his faves), he will lay down inside and take a nap. This little man is a great car companion as well! He will jump right into his seat and lay down and occasionally prop up to the window to see the view and, if you let him, get some sniffs through the window.


Colby's been a sweetheart and deserves a fur-ever home that will show him the same unconditional love they will get from him in return.  Interested in adoption? Make sure you have an application filled out on our website at www.austincockerrescue.org and email us at woof@austincockerrescue.org. We are not accepting out of state applications at this time.

animal.description:
Thor, approximately 6 yo, 80 lb neutered male lab/pit mix, UTD on shots and on preventatives, is still looking for his forever home 
.
*his needs are very specific. If you meet 

Thor's checklist, in exchange you will receive the most loving, intelligent dog imaginable. 

Thor would also benefit from a foster home within a two hour radius of Virginia Beach. 

Thor loves people, walks, toys and couch time. He is house broken and for the most part respectful of things when you are away. Now and then, there may be a dish towel pulled down or a couple of your possessions on the floor. I have never seen him tear up anything, except on rare occasion, a paper towel. His ideal would be someone working from home or retired, Thor will patiently stay by your feet until your time is his. He is alpha and although he hasn't bitten another dog, he does try to mount them to show his dominance; therefore, he should be an only dog. We recommend no children and a quiet, nurturing home. Thor can be a talker but it is not over-the-top. Thor's back story is his Dad was tragically killed a year ago in a terrible traffic accident. Thor was shutdown for a long time, but now he is embracing the changes in his life and he's ready for his second chance. Overall, Thor corrects easily and is obedient to commands, which he definitely knows, but he is incredibly strong, a true powerhouse. He has a bit record from when he was a pup and still should be closely monitored when meeting people. Thor requires an alpha pack leader (human).He needs a person that is calm, firm and consistent with boundaries. With Thor, you will only win if you are mentally stronger than him and able to withstand his stubborn tendencies, especially in the beginning of your bond. In return, you will get a best friend. I don't say that lightly. Thor is a magnificent dog for the right owner. He has shown his grander to me and several fosters. Thor is incredibly smart and has the biggest heart for his person(s). He needs a smart owner. He wears his heart on his shoulder and he just wants to be with you. He loves to ride shotgun in the car. -don't let his age be a deterrent. Thor is the healthiest dog I know and he can out maneuver dogs a third of his age.

animal.description:
Meet Remi! She's an approx. 5-6 month old, 35 lb girl who we believe is a Dutch Shepherd mix. Due to her breed mix she has a ton of energy and doesn't like to be alone (she vocalizes this very well!), so apartments will be a no-go for Remi. She loves running, playing with toys and other dogs as well as snuggling her people. She does okay with cats right now, but her prey drive is pretty high so we'd prefer no cats in the home, as well as no children under 5 since she is a decent sized puppy and can be nippy when playing. Remi would prefer that her people be home more often than not and have a fenced in yard for her to run and play in! 

Go to www.foreverhomedogs.org to submit an application for Remi if you're interested. Her adoption fee will be $250.All adoptions are $200 per dog which include spay/neuter, micro-chipped and up-to-date on required shots. 

Senior dogs, at our discretion, are adopted out at $100 per dog because we know they will have less time with your family and may eventually have more needs as they get older. But we feel these dogs deserve to live out the rest of their lives as part of a loving family.

animal.description: This boy is definitely a unique looking boy with a very unique coloring. Notice the color on his head. He was turned into us as a lab and weimaraner mix due to his grey toned body. We actually think he is a lab, possibly weimaraner, with blue pit in him, a ""pittador"" as they are called. He is a very nice 50 pound boy who does great on a leash and seems to be kennel trained as he does go outside to go potty in his indoor and outdoor kennel. He was owned by a family who had him from 7 weeks and he has had lots of love in his life. He is a very well balanced and friendly boy who loves everyone. He would be a great family pet for an active family. He is now neutered and microchipped and fully vaccinated and ready to go. His adoption fee is $200 which covers his surgery and his medical work.

animal.description:
Hi yall, My name is Mahib and it means brave. My foster named me this because when I an my litter mates were found we had been out exploring while our mom was looking for food. My foster said that we were all brave puppies ready to explore a strange world, so she decided to give us all names that mean brave. See my mom was a stray dog and she took really good care of us. She had us hid under an old deserted barn so that we would safe and warm. When we were about 6 weeks old mom went out looking for food for her. While she was gone a couple of us decided to go exploring. A lady who lived nearby saw us before we could hide. She sent out the word to her friends and before the day was out we were all rescued. Now we have a warm doghouse and kennel to stay in until we can find our forever homes. Our foster mom has told us all about this place called Wisconsin where she says we will find our forever families. She said that there are wonderful people there who will treat us like family and will love us forever. She also told us that we will get to play in something she called snow. She said it was wet and cold but that she was sure we would love it. I don't know about my littermates, but I am excited, especially about the snow! I can't wait to meet my new family. If you think you need a little brave puppy, then please go to Sandipaws.org and complete the application to adopt. Can't wait to meet you! Licks and love, Mahib.
Thank you for your interest in a Sandi Paws Rescue, Inc. Please visit our site at sandipaws.org for more information on our organization or to fill out an application to adopt one of our pets. You can find information for volunteering o. our site as well.

animal.description:
My name is Dot and I'm a goofy, floppy puppy that loves to play non stop. My foster family likes to play the song Baby Shark while I try to puppy-bite their toes. I will need lots of play time, redirection with my puppy antics, and a family who is committed to helping me grow into my best, most well-behaved girl! I currently have foster canine, felines, and human siblings. I get along with all of them swimmingly! I am a true hound and as I grow will show my true natures- chasing, and baying. I will need a family who can help me channel my natural instincts and expose me to all the great parts of being a loved family member- with positive reward. 

Dots is a Hound puppy. Hounds are adorable and also high-energy. Hounds are typically bred for hunting and will likely have a very high prey drive, be vocal, and will need to have access to resources that will satisfy her energy level. Potential adopters should have a good understanding of the needs that come with having an active puppy and those of a working/hunting breed as well. Positive exposure and reinforcement are a must in her adoptive home, along with a solid plan for training and further socializing with other pets of all ages and sizes. 

To be considered, please start by applying online at caws.org. 
Dots's adoption fee is $300 and includes her fist year vaccines, spay and microchip. 

Please note that we carefully select each adoptive home to meet the needs of the animals in our care and not on a first come, first serve basis. Thanks! If you are interested in adopting a CAWS pet, please fill out an online application at https://caws.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Hello! My name is Ebenezer and I'm sort of a miracle dog myself. I'm an 8 year old, 16 lb shih tzu who had it rough for a while. I love people, I just want to snuggle. I am nearly blind but I get along pretty well. I learn my environment quickly and sometimes you can't even tell I'm blind. I do suffer from chronic dry eye and require daily eye drops and ointments. And I will admit, I'm not the easiest dog to take eye drops. :) I get along with everyone, dogs, cats, bunnies. I will tell you if I'm uncomfortable or surprised, with little nips, so ilI shouldn't be in a home with little kids. I came to CAWS with a large mass that was remofed and biopsy results came back benign. I have some bumps and lumps that are fatty masses but should be monitored. I am housetrained, I do ok in a crate, although I might whine. Overall I'm a sweet, mellow old man who just wants love, a warm doggie bed, and cuddles. 

Dogs are not placed on a first-come, first-serve basis. We strive to find the perfect home for each animal. Applications may take up to 48 hours to process.

All CAWS animals are fixed, microchipped, and vaccinated. His adoption fee is $200. If you are interested in adopting a CAWS pet, please fill out an online application at http://caws.org/adoption-application If you are interested in adopting a CAWS pet, please fill out an online application at https://caws.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Please read the animal bios completely before requesting additional information as we do our best to answer the most frequently ask questions in these bios. 

In order to adopt one of our animals an application must be submitted and approved. You can find these applications by going to http://humanemorgan.org/index.php?page=adoption 

ABOUT ADOPTING FROM THE HSMC: 
The shelter address is 1170 Fairground Rd. Madison, GA 30650. For more information on any of our pets, please feel free to email us at INFO@HUMANEMORGAN.ORG give us a call at 706-343-9977. 
All dogs are heartworm negative, current on vaccines/dewormings, and microchipped. 
All cats are FeLv/FIV negative, current on vaccines/dewormings, and microchipped. 
We are open 10am-5pm Monday-Saturday, we schedule our last adoption at 4pm everyday to allow our staff enough time to feed and walk dogs. 
We are an animal shelter and therefore are not able to individually potty train our residents. Many adult dogs do arrive ""house broken"" however due to animal behavior any change in environment will make an emotional impact on the animals and therefore initiate unwanted behaviors during the acclamation period. Please keep this in mind. Puppies do not have the biological maturity to maintain absolute bladder or bowel control and will require a certain degree of potty training and house breaking. Please consider the time and commitment it takes to provide the necessary building blocks for these special babies, prior to submitting your application. 
If you have any questions please email us at info@humanemorgan.org and provide name of the animal you are interested in, in the subject line. 
Thank you, HSMC Staff 

ADOPTION FEES Adoption Fees may change without notice. Always verify the fee when finalizing the adoption. 
~ Cats and Kittens ~ 
* Under 1 Year = $100 
* 1-5 Years = $75 
* Over 5 Years = $50 
** Purebred cats and kittens may be subject to special pricing 

~ Mix Breed Dogs ~ 
* Under 1 Year = $200 
* 1 -3 Years = $175 
* 4-8 Years = $150 
* Over 8 Years = $100

~ Purebred and Designer Breed Dogs ~ 
* Under 1 Year = $375 
* 1-3 Years = $350 
* 4-8 Years = $275 
* Over 8 Years = $150 

~ Medical and Special Needs ~ 
We have rescued dogs and cats which require additional medical care or that have special needs which are not life threatening. In these cases we may require a higher fee to help recoup the costs of their care while at our rescue.

animal.description:
***All animals listed on our website are in private foster homes. To arrange a meet and greet with a dog, you MUST fill out the adoption application so that it can be sent to the foster parent for review to determine if your home is a match for the dog. If a dog receives multiple applications, we operate on a best-fit basis, not first come first served.***

Peanut Butter is an extremely intelligent, playful, and energetic - yet well-mannered young man. He does not like being left alone, but, can be taught that it is OK for short periods. He would love to have another playmate though and has done well with everything from small Feist mixes to Great Danes and everything in-between at his foster home. He is a ""strong"" chewer that would do better with harder chew toys or bones as he may pick the stuffing out of soft toys, but, he is easily corrected if you happen to catch him.

He sits, shakes, sits before his meals and waits to be told to ""go ahead"" to eat, comes when he is called, and can be exuberant on a leash, but, again - is easily corrected and with time, should walk like a dream. If left without exercise and mental stimulation though, Peanut Butter could find all kinds of new holes to dig in your yard and/or turn your indoor space into a full-speed race-track.

Peanut Butter is a lover who craves your attention and likes to be near his family, especially cuddling, both human and furry.

He is up to date on vaccinations, neutered, microchipped, dewormed, and on heartworm and flea/tick prevention. The adoption fee is $300. If you think Peanut Butter could be the one for you, please fill out an adoption application on our website: www.secondchancenc.org. Thank you!

animal.description:
Miss Bea was hit by a car and taken to the local shelter with a compound fracture to her back leg. She went to a local vet and received pain meds and basic care, but her owner never claimed her. The decision was made to amputate her leg but the shelter could not afford to pay for the surgery. Donation requests were shared on social media and the money was raised for her surgery! A wonderful and loving foster home was found and Miss Bea is thriving, healing and full of energy. Her adoption fee will cover her upcoming spay and Heartworm test.

01/11/21 - Amputation of back right leg

01/11/21 - Parvo/Distemper and Rabies vaccination

01/26/21 - Microchip

animal.description:
BamBam loves to dance! He has been dancing for his dinner at the shelter - up on his hind legs twirling around. He is about a year old and true to his chihuahua DNA - he is charming, alert with a big-dog attitude. He plays well with dogs his size and the big boys. BamBam has been observed to be good with kids. He is now safe in a foster home out in the country. He could live in the city or country as long as he has a human side-kick. 

BamBam will require training to become his best self, as he's little and jumpy - it's best to have manners at any size. Special care should be taken in cold weather since BamBam has never seen snow and he is a southern dog with a short coat. He's the right size to dress up, though it will be a new experience to him. He is affectionate and loves to be held, he can be wiggly when he's ready to play again.

The adoption fee is $600.00. He is up to date on vaccines according to age, has received proper deworming, and comes with additional dewormer if needed. This pet is microchipped, spayed, comes with 2-6 months of Heartworm preventative, and one month free trial of pet insurance if registered by adopter with insurance company. All animals receive a health certificate (stating that a licensed veterinarian saw the pet and deemed it healthy for travel, but is not a promise of perfect health.) Our transports are USDA certified and the cost of transport is included in adoption fee!

 

He is currently being fostered in Houston, Tx but will be traveling to the PNW on 02-06-2021 and arriving 2-3 days later in Washington. 

 

Due to the Covid-19 crisis we are experiencing a dramatic influx in inquiries and adoption applications. If you have questions regarding a pup you are interested in please fill out an adoption application. Once received it can take up to a week to complete our review. Be assured we have received your received your application! If you need more information regarding a pup you are interested in, the process of filling out an adoption application is still required prior to answering detailed questions. We value our potential adopters time and appreciate your patience as our staff navigate through the blessing of an overwhelming response for adoptions.

 

Please inquire by submitting an application (Application link here) : https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/30255/generic 

Questions, Adoption Coordinator - leah@threelittlepittiesrescue.org

 

Please go to our website to see more about our rescue and what we do! We are very proud of our hard work in saving as many animals as we can, giving them what they need, and matching them with the right families.

animal.description:
Did someone ask for a sweet, pretty, and petite GSD mix? Well thats me, Freya aka Zena! Im about 1 year old, 62lbs, and have medium-high energy. I originally grew up with my big sister by my side, and now I have a husky foster sister, so I enjoy having dog friends. Youll win me over with neck scritches and belly rubs, so you better expect to give me some love often I would really love a home with a fenced backyard, as Im happiest when I get to explore and play with a doggy and then get some attention from you. Im currently getting used to crate training and will need a family to work on general training (positive reinforcement only). Im also working on potty training, mainly because I sometimes get nervous and a little pee comes out (oopsies!). Cant wait to love a forever family of my own!

If you are interested in adopting, please visit our website and complete an adoption application at www.elpasocountycanine.org/adopt

animal.description:
Hi, I am Siri, a Lab/Pointer Mix and I am almost 3 months old. I am a bit shy at first but once I get comfortable I am a very energetic puppy that loves to run and play. I love toys and with the help of my sister , Pixel, we find those crazy squeakers and kill them after we play with them some more. I know sit and I am working on my other commands. Im also learning to walk on the leash not so sure about that yet. I will kennel up (especially if treats are involved). Im your typical rambunctious pup that just keeps on going. I really like people and love to get in lots of snuggles and kisses. I enjoy playing and wrestling with Pixel. I have not played with other dogs yet but have met the neighbors bigger dogs and love to visit with them through the fence. I have not been exposed to cats. I will need someone with patience that is willing to work with me on basic commands and potty training as I am not fully potty trained. You will need to teach me where to go and how to ask until I get the hang of it. I kennel at night and when my foster family is away. If you are looking for a puppy that will want LOTS of attention and you have the patience for a puppy, I may be what you are looking for. I will need toys or chew bones to keep me occupied, maybe a playmate and of course lots of snuggles and kisses from you.

I am ready to move into my new home anytime. I am scheduled to be spayed, I have been microchipped, dewormed and received my puppy shots along with rabies. My adoption fee is $400. Apply for me at www.bassetandbeagle.org if you are ready for a forever companion. I am currently fostered in Omaha NE.

animal.description:
Hello there everyone, my name is Bailey! I'm a 1-year-old pup around 40# with a beautiful chocolate coat, kind amber brown eyes, and adorable merle booties. To be honest with you, my foster mom cannot say enough good things about me; I have a golden personality - I'm lovable, friendly to all people, great with other dogs, and I live to please. 

I'm kid-friendly, and I have never met a stranger. I have a great energy level and am the perfect balance between playful and a couch potato. I love being pet and spending time with my people, especially cuddling up next to you on the couch. I'm good with other dogs of all sizes and ages - I'm in a foster home with a morkipoo, a golden, a blind senior Boston, and my puppies. I'm very kind, patient, and gentle with my puppies. My foster mom thinks it is so sweet how I will pick up my toys and take it to them so they can play with me. 

I'm a smart pup who is highly motivated to be a good girl. I walk well on a leash and know several commands like 'sit', 'down' and 'paw' (and I love getting treats when I do them). You don't need to crate me when I'm home alone either because I'm not destructive. I also come when my name is called - I will come right up to you and put my paws on your lap or rest my head against you. My ideal home would be one with children or another dog to play with or someone who enjoys going on nice walkies every day. I'm a total sweetheart and a such a gem! I know I'll make my future person or people very happy.


My adoption fee is $200. This includes a spay/neuter, up-to-date vaccines, deworming, a microchip, a heartworm test, and, if needed, heartworm treatment.

animal.description:
RCHS does not conduct DNA tests on dogs who enter our facility therefore we are unable to guarantee breed or breed mix. Information provided by shelter staff, volunteers, and veterinarians is used to give a best estimate as to a dog's breed make up. We do our best to inform adopters about the potential breeds for each dog.

We are a dog only facility so we do not know how most of our dogs will be with cats. Even if a dog is surrendered to us and said to be good with cats there is no way to be sure the dog will be good with your cats. We do have a 7 day foster-to-adopt program so that you can see how the dog interacts with your cats before adoption.

animal.description:
*Due to concerns surrounding COVID-19, we have reformatted the way that we do adoptions in order to follow social distancing protocols. We are thrilled that so many people want to adopt right now, but we are not equipped to handle the large number of calls, applications, and email inquiries we are receiving. We are no longer answering phone calls and are doing all communications with adopters via email. If you have a dog you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application before sending us emails. When your application has been processed, you will receive an email from us with further instructions on how to adopt. You do not need a new application for every dog that you are interested in adopting. 

At MAMCO we understand that in order to continue rescuing moms and babies, we must stretch our finances as far as we are able. For this reason we use variable adoption pricing. By assigning higher adoption fees to high demand moms and puppies, we are able to rescue more families in need.The money raised through these adoptions acts as a benefactor to moms and puppies in our care who require expensive veterinary treatments, have behavioral issues, or need more time to find a home. We often reduce the adoption fees on these harder-to-place moms and puppies to help them find forever families. Adoption fees vary, but all include spay or neuter, microchip, up to date vaccinations and deworming, rabies vaccine at the time of spay or neuter, and 30 days of pet insurance. We also cover hernia repair and cherry eye repair at the time of spay or neuter. Applications can be filled out at mamcorescue.org.

animal.description: Theo is a little 2 year old Chihuahua, about 12 pounds and is full of love. He has some wounds on his back and he won't tell us what happened (he just wants to forget) but they could either be from a dog fight or from a bird trying to grab him. Either way, he's ready to find a new forever home who will love him and keep him safe!All animals are altered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, licensed (dogs). Cats tested for FELV/FIV. Dogs tested for Heartworm. All animals are available to the first family that is a good match, and if we have more than one animal who is a good match, there will be a lottery for all matches. Note that families must have come in to our adoption center and spoken with an adoption counselor prior to any lottery (when we have lotteries, they usually occur on Saturday mornings).

animal.description: Meet our beautiful Sadie. She came to us in distress after her owner died and the family could not keep her. She went to the county pound where she struggled like many dogs do and then on to a home for a few months where an aggressive dog gave her a hard time. Unfortunately, while there she was kept in a room by herself for long periods of time which made her sad. When we got her she was scared and nervous and it's taken her a few weeks with us to decompress. She is still a nervous girl who needs a lot of patience and love. She has trouble meeting people especially men and we are working with the CFP trainers who have taught us how to let her warm to people at her own pace. We introduced her to several other foster dogs, and she did well, but she is not okay with all dogs especially smaller dogs. We think Sadie would do best in an only dog home with a loving experienced owner. We give her free reign in the house, and she has never chewed, is not high energy and is fully house trained. She loves her walks and is learning her leash manners. A home with a fenced yard would be ideal because she blossoms when she is outside running around and is as happy as can be. She is the cutest little girl but does not make a good first impression because she is shy and nervous of new situations. On her walks and in our yard, she loves to sniff and hunt squirrels and is a happy soul. After a few weeks with us she is loving and affectionate and we are sure she will make someone a perfect companion. Her big dark eyes will melt your heart so come see Sadie and give her a chance at a forever home. If you are interested in this animal please start by filling out an adoption application at CFP-NC.org/adopt and we will get in touch with you.

animal.description:
Meet Sandy! She is a 2-year-old, 50lb female Hound mix. What can her foster mom say about Sandy? Sandy is a lovable, caring, fun, energetic, and spunky dog. She loves lots of attention, likes long walks and does well on leash. Sandy has a lot of energy so she needs a place to run around and work out the zoomie, a nice fenced yard would be great for her getting her. She could do well in an apartment as long as she gets her walks and exercise each day.

Sandy seems to be dog friendly and it's recommended that she would do better in a setting with older kids. She is learning not to jump and currently is doing well. Most importantly Sandy is house trained and is crate trained which is great! She does well when she is in her crate while alone. Sandy likes toys but she is a chewer, so would do well with durable toys and things to keep her occupied. In the end of the day shell be the first one to lay on the couch and cuddle with you. Sandy is looking for a loving home with her furever family to love her and play with her.

As part of Sandy's $250 adoption fee, she is spayed, microchipped, up to date on vaccines, and current on her monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. If you have questions about this sweet girl, you can email Dogteam@pawsforlifenc.org. If you wish to adopt Sandy, you can fill in an online application for her under the Adopt a Pet Tab on our website: www.pawsforlifenc.org.

animal.description:
Sweet momma Milan was rescued from an absuive situation and luckily brought to Muddy Paws in time to comfortably give birth on 1/13/2021. More information will be posted as the babies start to explore the world and show their personalities. They will be ready to go to new homes on 3/10/2021. Please check back for pupdates!

Since this puppy may be too young to be altered at the time of adoption, the adopters will be provided with a voucher to have the puppy altered and microchipped by the time she is 6 months of age. This must be done at Nebraska Humane Society. If you prefer to take the puppy to your own vet, we will pay a PORTION of the cost ($69) to your vet of choice

The suggested adoption donation for this puppy is $450. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes.

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver.

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months.

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

Sweet momma Milan was rescued from an absuive situation and luckily brought to Muddy Paws in time to comfortably give birth on 1/13/2021. More information will be posted as the babies start to explore the world and show their personalities. They will be ready to go to new homes on 3/10/2021. Please check back for pupdates!

Since this puppy may be too young to be altered at the time of adoption, the adopters will be provided with a voucher to have the puppy altered and microchipped by the time he is 6 months of age. This must be done at Nebraska Humane Society. If you prefer to take the puppy to your own vet, we will pay a PORTION of the cost ($69) to your vet of choice

The suggested adoption donation for this puppy is $450. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes.

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver.

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months.

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

Rainier:

Like his namesake, this pup has a face of photo perfection and will be the object of many a photo in his lifetime. With his brindle coloration he is uniquely beautiful. He is the smallest of our marvelous mountain pups, but he is BIG on personality. His adventurous spirit and overt friendliness are sure signs of a pup with a confident, sweet nature. We know from his howl that there is certainly some breed of hound in his DNA. He is quite active, agile, curious and loves to explore. Therefore, he will need a fenced yard to keep him safe. 
 

Rainier is neutered, microchipped and on prevention.

animal.description: Hagrid is such a go-with-the-flow dude. This affectionate boy is happy to snuggle on the couch with you if you're watching a movie or working. He loves lounging on his back and getting petting and belly rubs. He's also so excited to go for a walk, and come back home to play with his favorite stuffed squirrel toy. He can entertain himself by tossing around his kongs and lacrosse balls. This polite boy usually walks well on his leash; he pulls when he's excited to see other dogs and new people he wants to meet so he could use some continued training. He will go right up to people for some pets. He also likes hanging out in the backyard, running along the fence to greet the neighbor dogs. As a smartie pants, he understands what 'sit,' 'down' and 'shake' mean, and is learning about other commands. He's also a house-trained pup who's making progress on crate training. This chill, well-behaved boy will be a great fit in a wide variety of homes. He would love to have a doggie housemate, and for sure hopes for love and affection from his humans - and petting and treats. Come meet your future cuddle buddy! He'll follow you home.

animal.description: Mrs. Pickles is a sweet and loving lady who would love nothing more than to snuggle up next to you on the couch and give you kisses. She's a loyal companion who wants to stay by your side. This mature lady has plenty of spunk, and youthful energy to play with her squeaky toys and chomp on bones. A good bone or toy keeps her calm and busy. She also loves to go on short strolls and sniff all those interesting things outside. Mrs. Pickles is smart and keen to learn, and seems to pick up training quickly! She knows how to 'sit' and 'shake,' and is a pretty good listener. She may be a big gal, but she walks well on the leash, doesn't get easily distracted, and will stay by your side. She's very treat-motivated, but needs few treats to make sure she remains at a healthy weight. She's also a house-trained girl who does really well in her crate when she's home alone. She is looking for a cozy place to call home and a forever companion to share snuggles with. Come meet her!

animal.description: If awards were given for tail wagging, Edric would win a prize! His tail wags and wags. This very sweet boy is so happy to be in a kind home with humans he trusts. He loves to gaze at humans with his kind eyes. Edric is a calm, gentle boy who's also encountered dogs on his walks, and even in a coffee shop he visited. He's mildly curious and wags his tail at them, and at new humans he meets. He likes everyone! He walks well on his leash, wagging at silly squirrels. At home, he's happy to lay down next to his people, including his teenage housemate. Plus, he's house-trained and does well in his crate, going in for a snooze. Edric is a patient, quiet boy who would love a home with playful humans. He is heartworm positive, but all that means is that he'll need a couple of months of rest during treatment, at APA!'s expense. Come meet this tail wagger, he'll be so happy to see you.

animal.description: Nellie Fur-dog-o is like a bird who wants to fly away from the shelter and into your home! This exceptionally sweet lady loves her people -- and the occasional hot dog. She likes to snuggle and snore next to you on the couch or in bed, but also sometimes likes to do her own thing and snooze in the other room. She likes to be petted under her chin and on her chest as she slowly relaxes and falls asleep, as if hypnotized. Although Nellie is older, she is spunky and doesn't show many signs of it - her joints and vision seem as good as new. She can hear pretty well, and she trots along quickly on walks (though she could use someone to help her with her leash skills)! She is heartworm positive, but all that means is that she'll need a couple of months of rest during treatment, at APA!'s expense. Nellie is calmly affectionate and you can see her loving nature in her big brown eyes. She is crate-trained and knows to head in there for bedtime with her stuffed unicorn. She also hangs out in her crate calmly when left home alone. She's house-trained (just show her where to go at first, as with all dogs!) and she is not a barker. In fact, her foster has only heard her bark once! She would prefer a home where people are home a decent amount of time so she can get her pets, and would probably prefer to be the only animal in the house, though she may do fine with another dog. Nellie would love to meet you, show you her wags, get your petting, and head home with you to be your TV binge buddy. Come meet her today!

animal.description: JETSKI, 5 years old, is 1 of 4 dogs surrendered to CCHS on 1/20/21 for hoarding. He's a solid, 80 lb. hunk of a Terrier who sasses you with plenty of barking when penned. Jetski's most unusual trait is the peculiar goat, or baying, groan that he makes when he's lonely. The first time you hear him make this sound, you'll find yourself stopping dead in your tracks searching for an animal you don't own, then laughing when you realize it's Jetski! That pretty much sums up Jestki. He's goofy, lively, friendly and sweet. Jetski's a good walker, sits immediately when he hears the treat bag and sits on command. He's a leaner and despite his low rider carriage, he occasionally tries to jump up and put his paws on you. Jetski's adoption fee is $150. He is altered, current on shots, wormed, microchipped and treated with monthly heart worm, flea and tick preventive.

animal.description:
This is Ginger! She is a 5 1/2 year old mixed breed pup who weighs 22 pounds. Ginger came to us with her sister, Tulip. They are a sweet bonded pair who are ready to find their forever home together.

Ginger and Tulip were extremely fearful when they first came to us. They've spent some time in a loving foster home and it's really helped them start learning how to trust people. It took them some time to become comfortable in their foster home and we expect the same will happen in their forever home. Because of this, an extremely patient and understanding adopter will be important. It will take time for them to be comfortable with a new person showing them affection. Once they trust you, these girls are the sweetest cuddle bugs. They are loving, low-key, and quiet - they'd prefer a home where their humans are the same. They are crate trained, potty trained, and do well with cats and other dogs.

Ginger looks up to Tulip and will follow her lead. Out of the two, Ginger takes longer to open up and trust new people. She is more fearful of the male in her foster home and only recently has started to become comfortable with him. 

The minimum adoption fee for Ginger and Tulip is $375 plus a $12 fee per dog for rabies registration for McLean County residents.

She has been spayed, microchipped, vaccinated, heartworm checked, dewormed, and is on flea and heartworm preventatives.

To be considered for adoption, you must first submit the application found at: 
 http://fs16.formsite.com/WishBoneCanineRescue/adoptionapplication/index.html

For information about this dog's breed(s), visit: http://www.dogbreedinfo.com/abc.htm

If you would like to make Joy a part of your family please go to www.barktownrescue.org and fill out an adoption application.
Joy's Adoption Fee: $170The shelter software system requires that we choose a predominant breed or breed mix for our dogs. Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable so for most of our dogs we are only guessing at the dog's predominant breed or breed mix. We strongly encourage you to select your new pet by looking at each dog's individual personality and pet qualities rather than relying on a breed label that is only our best guess.

Our adoption fees vary from $150 and up. All of our dogs are up to date on vaccines, heart worm preventives, and flea/tick medication, and will be spayed/neutered prior to adoption. animal.description:
This is Tulip! She is a 5 1/2 year old mixed breed pup who weighs 18.2 pounds. Tulip came to us with her sister, Ginger. They are a sweet bonded pair who are ready to find their forever home together.

Ginger and Tulip were extremely fearful when they first came to us. They've spent some time in a loving foster home and it's really helped them start learning how to trust people. It took them some time to become comfortable in their foster home and we expect the same will happen in their forever home. Because of this, an extremely patient and understanding adopter will be important. It will take time for them to be comfortable with a new person showing them affection. Once they trust you, these girls are the sweetest cuddle bugs. They are loving, low-key, and quiet - they'd prefer a home where their humans are the same. They are crate trained, potty trained, and do well with cats and other dogs.

Tulip is the more confident of the two. In her foster home, she was the first one to start accepting pets and snuggles. She seems to show Ginger the ropes.

The minimum adoption fee for Ginger and Tulip is $375 plus a $12 fee per dog for rabies registration for McLean County residents.

She has been spayed, microchipped, vaccinated, heartworm checked, dewormed, and is on flea and heartworm preventatives.

To be considered for adoption, you must first submit the application found at: 
 http://fs16.formsite.com/WishBoneCanineRescue/adoptionapplication/index.html

For information about this dog's breed(s), visit: http://www.dogbreedinfo.com/abc.htm

animal.description:
***Please DO NOT send us inquiries/emails asking if this dog is still available. If a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder- we are still accepting applications for them**

Fargo is currently in Houston, TX and can transport to the PNW mid February. 

Fargo, 1.5 years old, Shephard mix, 61 lbs, male. This amazing dog was found wandering around a neighborhood. No one came looking for him so his finders reached out to us to help find him a forever home. 

Fargo is in a foster home with other dogs and plays really well with his female foster sister. One of the male dogs is not so friendly so Fargo stays clear of him. They are able to be separate in the yard so when Fargo sees him he wags his tail while the other dog just barks at him. Fargo does not charge the fence, but rather walks away. 

We have no history with cats. If you are considering applying for Fargo and have cats please have a way to keep them separate as Fargo settles in. 

Fargo has not been around young kids, but the foster's adult son has a medical condition and he is very gentle with him, not jumping up and waits to be petted. 

He does have a lot of energy and is a larger dog. He does still want to jump when he first sees the foster but responds to down and sit. Due to his size and energy we recommend a home with children 12 years and older. 

Fargo could use some practice on leash as he tends to pull and is strong.  He rides in the car really well, mostly sitting up in the seat like a person. 
He knows a few commands and is housebroken. 
He has mild separation anxiety and will pant and paces until his foster mom returns home. He has not been destructive during this time. 

The current foster home has a 5 foot fence that he has almost been able to jump over. Fargo will need a 6 foot fence or higher to ensure he doesn't get out. 

He does have some food aggression and should be separate. As we don't know much about his history, we can assume he may have developed some resource guarding from being a stray. He also eats his food extremely fast and would benefit from a slow feeder.  He loves treats, he takes them very gently. He loves peanuts and will eat them gently out of your hand like a horse.

Fargo is very loving, he loves giving kisses and getting belly rubs.. He also loves to have between his eyes rubbed sometimes it will put him to sleep.

IF you have prior or current shepherd experience that is a huge benefit. Understanding his breed, personality and quirks will make for a successful journey. 

Fargo is a young active dog who will need a secure yard or an active home. He will need some support on leash training. Fargo will need time to decompress and settle into a new home.

***Listed BREED and AGE - We are taking our best guess on age, breed and size when fully grown. We rarely know a dog's exact age nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time.

The first step in our process is filling out an application. We will review your application as soon as we are able- there are two of us and we do the best that we can. We review applications on a first come first serve basis and look for the best fit/match for dog and applicant.

https://heartoftheunderdog.org/adoption-application

Adopter Must Have German Shepherd Experience, Enroll in Training, and Have Fenced in Yard.Adopter Must Have German Shepherd Experience, Agree to Home Visit, Enroll in Training, and Have Fenced in Yard. **No Exceptions. Please do not apply unless you meet and agree to all criteria**
Meet Max! Max is a 10 month old GSP. Max is friendly with other dogs of similar size and energy or could be your one and only. Kids should be 12+ due to his size. Max is trainable, affectionate, full of life, friendly and entertaining. Max requires a fenced in yard. Adopter must have experience with the GSP breed, and agree to enroll in training. A home visit is also required during the adoption process. If you are interested in adopting Max please fill out an adoption application at www.barktownrescue.org

Adoption Fee: $170The shelter software system requires that we choose a predominant breed or breed mix for our dogs. Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable so for most of our dogs we are only guessing at the dog's predominant breed or breed mix. We strongly encourage you to select your new pet by looking at each dog's individual personality and pet qualities rather than relying on a breed label that is only our best guess.

Our adoption fees vary from $150 and up. All of our dogs are up to date on vaccines, heart worm preventives, and flea/tick medication, and will be spayed/neutered prior to adoption. Portions of your adoption fee also help care for the sick and injured animals that we take in. Thank you for supporting us and considering a rescue dog!

**Due to an abundance of interest in adoption (YAY!!!), we are currently unable to respond to all emails (there’s just one of me), to apply please use our fillable app and be sure to list the pet’s name as Teddy so that Google Forms files it correctly, link here:  https://forms.gle/89f61WrrQL1cRCbD8 **

This adorable little dude is Teddy, a 14lb bundle of joy!  Teddy is fully vetted and around a year old.  He’s great with dogs and cats (But will bark at them), and ADORES children.  I’m struggling with guessing his breed, so I went with long haired chi and terrier.  He’s bursting with personality and wiggles.  Teddy is a door darter, so his new home will need to be vigilant to prevent him from escaping.  He is not hypoallergenic!  Like many small breed dogs, Teddy will still have an occasional accident, but his foster mom is working hard to have him fully housebroken for his new home.

*Edited to add:  Teddy is a high energy small dog syndrome kind of guy - not a purse dog or a home decoration :). No apartments, as he has a piercing bark when playing or complaining!

Again, please apply using our fillable app link above.  Info requests and emails will not be answered at this time.  Thank you for your interest in adoption, and for your understanding during this crazy time!

animal.description:
Hello world! My name is Cricket, and I am a sweet 3-1/2 year-old coonhound in search of my forever home. 

I am a typical hound in many ways: I am laid back and not the in-your-face kissy type. My foster mom describes me as "pretty chill." I follow my nose everywhere, especially if it leads me to yummy treats, and I will sit and shake for them before taking them gently. I am housebroken, but I like privacy when I do my business, so I will need a physical fenced-in yard. My foster mom introduced me to this crate thing, and while I didn't love it at first, I now go in willingly and settle down for the night.

Even though I am a long-legged girl and weigh 70 pounds, I do not like other big dogs. I adore the small dog in my foster home and am uninterested in cats. I don't bother them and they don't bother me. I am good with children, as long as they are not intimidated by my size.  I like to be with my humans as much as possible, and I would love to join a family that doesn't leave me alone for long periods of time. I may seem a little aloof at first when meeting new people, but I get attached quickly. I have so much love to give and will make a great companion.

Our adoption fee is $260 for dogs over 5 months of age and includes all vaccinations, spay/neuter, micro chip implantation and registration/transfer, heartworm test and much more. Puppies up to 5 months of age are $275 and this includes all sets of puppy vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip implantation and registration and more. To adopt, go to www.fosterpetoutreach.org to complete an application.
Please note: Foster Pet Outreach tries to limit our adoptions to an area within approximately 60 miles of Peoria, Illinois.

Reba is a very sweet-tempered mountain cur and Labrador mix who on 12/4/20 gave birth to eight healthy puppies. She has just finished weaning them and is enjoying a little independence at her foster home as you can see in the photos. She is excellent with her puppies. She loves other dogs and loves kids! She would not be suitable for a home with cats. Reba is a young adult, weighing sixty-eight pounds, very healthy, and fully vaccinated. We chose not to spay her yet due to her recent litter of five boys and three girls. As of 1/27/21, most of the puppies have been adopted. The 6-week weights of the ones who MAY (not promising) still be available are Elvis at 11 lbs. and Brooks at 11.8 lbs. We will cover Reba’s spay expense once she is settled in her new home with a rescue-friendly veterinarian. At this time, it is possible that one of her puppies may be available to be adopted with her as well depending on when your application is received. To adopt Reba please visit our website www.peace4paws.org and fill out an adoption application. Thanks! 


Dog Size Guidelines:
Small: 25 lbs and under (11 kg)
Medium: 26–60 lbs (12 – 27 kg)
Large: 61–100 lbs (28 – 45 kg)
Extra Large: 101 lbs or more (46 kg)

animal.description:
Meet Lucy! She is about 2 years old, 40 pounds, and looks like she has some hound in her mix. Lucy was brought into the shelter with a broken femur and 10 puppies! In addition, she had complications from her spay surgery. Her leg also had trouble healing and ultimately she had to have it amputated. She is now healthy, her puppies are adopted and she is ready for her very own forever home. She is doing great with house training at her foster home, crate trained, and plays well with other dogs. She could go to a home with kids 8+ or other dogs. She needs an active home with lots of short walks/hikes, and needs to be one of the family. She needs someone that will increase her socialization, particularly with new people. She's a very friendly loving girl but can get scared & barky around unfamiliar things.

Her foster says, "At her vet, they call Lucy the "miracle girl". She survived a very serious pyometra surgery. One of the worst they'd seen. She fought very hard post op and has come out a playful, active, happy, loving girl. Because a portion of her bladder had to be removed, we've been using Proin and an herbal supplement. Accidents in the house are basically non existent and she now sits by the door and indicates with a bark when she wants to go out. I classify her as housebroken.
Shortly after that, she was hit by a car and sustained a broken humerous. Lucy is vocal when she plays with our other dog and plays very nicely, never a problem. She's been great around even unfamiliar dogs.

She is obsessed with her collection of stuffed animals (especially loves the ones that squeak or even better, talk to her). She's a great eater and loves treats and bully sticks. I seat belt her in the back and she seems to really enjoy rides in the car. As mentioned above, she needs continued socialization and confidence with strangers and getting used to walking on leash past moving cars. We've had her almost 2 months and I have never, ever seen one sign of aggression or anger. She will charm you with the genuine love in her eyes and the way she just wants to be with and cuddle with you. We love this girl and am certain her new family will feel the same.."

She is available for direct adoption with an approved adopter in North Dartmouth, MA on February 5th. Please fill out an application at www.browndogcoalition.com/adoption.

- Please thoughtfully discuss with your entire household the physical, financial, and emotional responsibilities of a puppy/dog BEFORE applying to adopt.
- Our adoption process has been adapted for social distancing and may be different for every dog. Please fill out an application, and we will explain that dog's process as needed.
- Puppies/dogs may not be given as gifts or surprises.
- More information about our adoption process, application and adoption fee can be found at browndogcoalition.com

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Twyla. I’m approximately 4 years old and 30 lbs. I’m a lab mix, although I’m much smaller than your typical lab. 
I’ve realized as I’m learning to be a lady that I enjoy the finer things in life, such as a nice dog bed for getting my beauty rest throughout the day. 
I prefer a quieter home, and if you have a dog I get along best with friends that are older. I certainly wouldn’t mind at all if I’m the only dog. 
I’ve been through a lot in life so I like that I can now live my best life. (I’m the proud momma to the Schitt’s Creek litter.) Ido get scared in unfamiliar places, especially when there are loud sounds. I recently learned how to walk on a leash and and enjoy taking my foster mom’s lead. 
I am also crate trained, but if I’m in a comfy spot before bed you’ll have to bribe me to get up and go to bed. I’m still learning to potty train, but while learning I know to use puppy pads. I’m heartworm positive, but have already begun treatment. I promise to love you forever and cannot wait to met you!

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2020 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

animal.description:
Please go to www.yvpr.org/adoptions for more information and to complete your application.**  

Meeka is an gorgeous Siberian Husky born November 23, 2017. She is 24 inches tall and 54 lb, and looks crisp and pretty as if she just came from the Arctic. She has a stunning coat of cream and brown, and her eyes are beautiful. 
She gets along well with other dogs and is playful with them. She will chase cats but has never harmed them. She will chase chickens. She has been around a 7 month old child and has done fine. She's house trained and will pace at the door to signal. She's crate trained. Meeka has a medium activity level. She spends her time both indoors and outside. She does well on a leash and loves walks. She will obey sit, lay down and shake commands but needs a little work.  She will allow bathing and brushing and that's why she's such a fine looking dog! Meeka is playful. She loves tug of war. She likes playing in sprinklers. She doesn't know how to fetch but will entertain herself and observing humans playing ball by herself.  Meeka would be a nice dog for adopters with a secure yard and some knowledge of Huskies. She needs a little more training, plenty of attention and activities to keep her busy. She's ready for her forever home. Please apply for Meeka at yvpr.org/adoptions!

An application must be filled out and accepted before a meet can be set up. If accepted, you will hear from us within 72 hours. You will have the opportunity to ask questions before you meet the pet; an adoption may or may not happen at that time. We do adopt outside the Yakima area IF you are able to come to Yakima to pick up your adopted pet.  We do not have a kennel facility; all of our pets are in foster homes. Therefore, meets and adoptions take place at either our office or at a place chosen by the foster.   If a pet has 'pending' beside its name, an adoption is imminent. Please fill out an application anyway because adoptions don't always go through. Your application will be kept on file for 30 days in case you find another pet you'd like to apply for.  Thanks for thinking adoption and Good Luck!

animal.description:
Gertie is a petite 43 lb senior mini-Chocolate Lab mix who is a friendly, gentle love bug. She greets new people with a wagging tail and kisses, and likes to curl up on the couch or get a belly rub.

Gertie plays tug of war with her foster's 2-year old dog, and gets along with the 1-year old cat. At age 7, she is quite mellow, but does like to play and take walks, where she is very curious and wags her tail when passing another dog. She has not barked at other dogs while out walking.
Gertie is working on her leash manners, as she pulls a bit, perhaps a little set in her ways at her age, but her foster is working on it! And so far, no accidents in the house! 


Unfortunately, because Gertie was not spayed until much later in life, she developed a malignant mammary tumor, Grade 1. The mass has been removed and she is doing great! However, she will need an owner that will need to understand that her life will likely be cut shorter than is deserved. But we hope that she can find a wonderful family that can give her the amazing final years she deserves! Given Gertie's condition, her adoption fee will be waived. PCR representatives are happy to address any questions about Gertie's condition. 

Gertie is spayed and up to date on vaccines and preventatives.

For more information, please contact France at fbognon@petconnectrescue.org

**If you're viewing this on Petfinder, please visit www.petconnectrescue.org to complete our non-binding application.**

animal.description:
Meet Azul, 
Azul is an owner surrender to not being a fan of little children. He would be best in a home with older children and as the only dog or with female dogs. So far he does seem to be fine with cats and has no reactions to them. Azul is overall a super sweet boy but just need to be in a home with no toddlers. With Blues it's not uncommon for hair lose and Azul does have thin hair on his back and signs of CDA which is very common in the color. Azul only needs to be microchipped and then will be ready to go to his forever home. 

All animals adopted from us are fully vetted including spay/neuter, vaccines, microchip, heartworm test and deworming. Please email us at HookedOnDobies@gmail.com, visit our Facebook page www.facebook.com/savingdobermankind or webpage https://www.savingdobermankind.org to request an application, inquire about an adoption fee, or to learn more! 

We do require a completed adoption application to be submitted before discussing details of a specific Doberman. 

We DO NOT have a central location, out foster homes are located throughout our geographic region including CO, WY, NM and TX.

We strive to PROTECT the privacy of out fosters. ALL Doberman meet and greets are conducted in a neutral meeting location made by appointment only.

animal.description: WE ARE GIVING PREFERENCE TO THOSE ADOPTERS WITH OTHER YOUNG PLAYFUL DOGS IN THE HOME. THE FIRST STEP IN THE PROCESS IS SUBMITTING AN APPLICATION. WE CANNOT ANSWER EMAILS ASKING ABOUT A DOG'S AVAILABILITY. IF IT IS LISTED WITHOUT THE WORD "PENDING" IT MEANS IT IS AVAILABLE. PLEASE COPY AND PASTE THIS LINK TO OUR APPLICATION: https://tlps.wufoo.com/forms/the-little-pink-shelter-adoption-application/ WE ARE GIVING PREFERENCE TO THOSE ADOPTERS WITH OTHER YOUNG PLAYFUL DOGS IN THE HOME. Cutie Patootie Alert!!! Seriously, look at this little face! Miss Maggie is one of the cuuuuutest little girls we've ever seen, and one lucky family is going to call her their own!! Maggie was bought by someone who fell in love with her as a tiny puppy but had no idea that puppies are living things that need time and attention. After a few months, they dumped Maggie at a high-kill shelter because she was "too much responsibility". And that's when we took responsibility and brought her into our group where she is getting all the time, attention and love she could ever want! Please build in extra time on your walks because Miss Maggie is so adorable you are bound to be stopped everywhere you go! Could she possibly be any cuter?!! And she is such a silly girl, running off her puppy crazies like a little lunatic until she's so tired she ends up falling over!! She loves her belly rubbed and flips over to show her belly at the slightest glance her way in hopes of yet another belly rub. She is super social with everyone at her foster home: the kids, their friends, the adults, the foster's dogs and cats. And if you pick her up for cuddles, she'll give you a thousand licks in return! Little Miss Maggie is about 7 months old, weighs about 7 - 8 pounds and is a very healthy girl. She's a mix of something small but we'll never know her true mix for certain. All we can be sure of is that she's full of personality and loves to prance! If you can promise Maggie a life of spoiling and love, please visit www.pinkshelter.org for more information about the adoption process. Full vetting, microchip, spay and transport from Arkansas included in her $1500 adoption fee. IF YOU HAVE AOL or YAHOO PLEASE CHECK YOUR SPAM FILE FOR OUR RESPONSE

animal.description:
Meet Holly! She is a beautiful, gorgeous 1yr old Lab mix. She is very tall, so there might be some Great Dane in there as well! Holly is a friendly goofy pup. Some of her favorite things include following her foster mom around, going on walks, squirrel watching and throwing small plush toys to herself. She is still a puppy so she enjoys to sleep. She is house trained and has good leash etiquette. She has learned how to sit, shake and laydown. She is good with other dogs (all sizes) and loves to play. She is very gentle with kids but due to her size we would recommend a home with older children. She would thrive in a home that had a backyard to run around in. Holly has a big personality and a big heart. She will be an amazing addition for some lucky person or family!

animal.description:
Please go to www.yvpr.org/adoptions for more information and to complete your application.**  
Sol is a German Shepherd mix female that is black and tan colored and she has a medium coat. She is 2 years old, 22 inches tall and 74 lb. Sol gets along with other dogs but would do best in a home without cats because she gets excited when seeing them. She has been around chickens and cattle and ignores them. She has been around children 2 and 3 years old and she has done fine. She will do okay in a crate for 2 hours or so but she has spent most of her time outdoors, therefore, we are uncertain weather she is housetrained. She is doing better on a leash but needs work, and she does not have training in commands. Sol has a medium energy level and she occasionally jumps on people but isn't too persistent in doing so. She is curious, adventurous,  loves to go on walks and loves toys. She likes being brushed. She enjoys being outdoors. Sol is highly intelligent and when she has a family of her own who are willing to consistently and patiently train her and make her secure with them she will be a quite loyal, loving, obedient and fun family member.  If you are interested in this great dog, please apply at yvpr.org/adoptions!


An application must be filled out and accepted before a meet can be set up. If accepted, you will hear from us within 72 hours. You will have the opportunity to ask questions before you meet the pet; an adoption may or may not happen at that time. We do adopt outside the Yakima area IF you are able to come to Yakima to pick up your adopted pet.  We do not have a kennel facility; all of our pets are in foster homes. Therefore, meets and adoptions take place at either our office or at a place chosen by the foster.   If a pet has 'pending' beside its name, an adoption is imminent. Please fill out an application anyway because adoptions don't always go through. Your application will be kept on file for 30 days in case you find another pet you'd like to apply for.  Thanks for thinking adoption and Good Luck!
