Louisiana is in search of an experienced adopter. Please read what her foster mom has to say about her below:

Louisiana aka Louise aka Miss Weezie is a very special lady, who came from a previously harder life. She is very fond of her people, but has never been taught how to appropriately show affection. She loves to snuggle and be petted, but is very much a DIVA, and would like it on her terms only. She would love nothing more than to be the center of your world, and loves to be wherever you are. She has a funny walk because of her knees, but no evidence that they are slowing her down!

She will likely need a more experienced dog owner, as she does have some behavioral tendencies that we are working with her on. She is potty trained and very smart, but is still suffering from some emotional trauma from her previous life.

She does currently live with dogs and cats, but I believe she would be more comfortable as an only pet who can be spoiled.

She will need lifelong medication for her eye issues but is very good at receiving her medications.

She has been settling very nicely into the routine of her foster life, and is looking for someone who may have the patience to help her adjust slowly.

She has a big heart and is full of love, and has improved so much since coming into our home. She is so spunky and full of life and she's hoping you may have room in your heart to help her really find her place and confidence!
Louisiana will need a very patient owner, who understands that everything will be on her terms. She does accept her eye medications with no fuss, and she always does well at the vet. She still has inappropriate reactions to certain stimuli, and may never be a warm cuddly, loves to be held/touched type of dog. But having said that, she does want attention, and can be very sweet! 

She is not perfect, and will not be the perfect dog for everyone, but we know there is someone that she would be the perfect dog for. Could that be you? 
BDRA has voted against the use of electrical fencing effective immediately.

animal.description:
Nibbles is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Nibbles is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~2 years 
Weight: ~33lbs
Housebroken: Yes
Crate trained: Has done well confined to a small area (kitchen) when his foster has been away for brief periods of time.
Dog sociability: Nibbles is selective with his dog friends and while he is not overtly aggressive/reactive, he will growl/is not interested in interacting with other dogs and should be a solo dog in his forever home.
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Unknown
Ideal home: Nibble is looking for a loving home in a quiet neighborhood. He will need to remain on restricted activity for the next ~9 months due to his heartworm.

Meet Nibbles! This small guy is so sweet and gentle. He is smart, too! He has mastered 'sit' in foster care and is ready and eager to learn even more tricks. Training will come in handy as this guy will need to be kept chill these next several months as he needs to be kept relatively calm due to his heartworm positive status. Nibbles loves to cuddle and will keep you warm this winter! 

Nibbles is heartworm positive and will be undergoing treatment at our Ellis Veterinary Clinic. OTAT will cover the cost of her treatment until he is heartworm negative. They will need to remain on exercise restriction for the next ~9 months. For information on the heartworm treatment process, visit: onetail.org/heartworm

Nibbles' adoption fee is 300. He is neutered, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm positive. He will require booster vaccines at the adopter's expense. He has a grade 1/4 locating patella which may cause intermittent. If lameness persists may require surgical intervention which will be the adopter's responsibility. Will be predisposed to arthritis in affected knee.

***We are receiving a much higher than usual number of adoption applications. We ask that you please be patient and someone will be in touch via email within 72 hours. Please do not email us unless you have not received a response in 72 hours. Please only fill out one adoption application. ***

animal.description: What do you think of when you hear the word Blue? The sky? The ocean? How about a big, handsome goofy dog?! With a happy personality like mine, you'd never know I have any ailments, right? Well, unfortunately the docs here discovered I have something called cancer. I'm not sure what that is, but I've been told it isn't a good thing. But I don't let it get me down. I'm still a happy boy and I'll be grateful to spend the rest of my life being your best friend. If you decide to bring me home, know that you are doing a very noble thing. Whatever length my life ends up being, my time can be joy-filled thanks to you.

animal.description:
Uluru came to our rescue back around April 2020.  He's aussie/cattle dog. He was bred by a farmer in Kentucky.  He was one of eleven in the litter.  All the puppies sold except for him and his sister. They got almost no human interaction.  At 11 months the farmer dumped them in a shelter.  They were so terrified that the shelter put them in a kennel in Kentucky and we didn't open the crate until the transport was in my backyard with the gate closed.  It was another 12 hours before they would venture out of their crate.  They were 99% feral essentially a wild dog .  Ru grew up protecting his sister from the farmer and who knows what.  He was fiercely protective of his sister. He would lung and bark to get me away from the two on them. His sister got adopted.

Uluru has made a lot of progress to becoming a companion dog.  He walks very well on a leash.  He sticks close to me outside.  He only barks at me when he wants me to play ball with him. He is very quiet in the house and loves his crate.  He needs a patient person that will let him become a companion at his own pace.

Ru's birthday is 3/30/2019. He is neutered, up to date on medical.  He weighs 36 pounds. Everyday he gets closer and closer.  He's gone from sleeping on the back porch to sleeping in the living room. He even sleeps in my bedroom now and then.  Because he is still part feral he must have an above ground fence.  Herding dog experience would be helpful. The adoption fee is $250.  To be considered for adopting Uluru please go to https://apbdogs.org/apply-for-adoption/   For more information email Glenna at Wishandaprayer@aol.com

animal.description:
Squirt & Bailey / Male / 10 Years / 15 & 8 lbs / Pomeranian Mix & Yorkshire Terrier / Brampton

Meet Squirt & Bailey! Although very much loved, bonded pair Squirt & Bailey were surrendered when their owner could no longer care for them. Bailey is a gentle soul who loves belly rubs and is not your typical “yappy” yorkie. Squirt loves to play with his ball and when he’s had enough, happily with settle down at your feet for a doze. Both love affection and bond closely with their people. They love to play and are happiest when with each other and their favorite humans.

Although Bailey can alert bark when new people startle him by knocking at the door, he generally meets people well and likes making new friends. Squirt is just as friendly and easy going with all people. They are both happiest when humans are around and like to follow people around all day. They have not been tested with young children but previous owners explained they don’t love babies or toddlers. They would do best with respectful children (ages 10+) that understand they are small and delicate.

Bailey has a tendency to chase after squirrels and can be a bit of an escape artist if left unattended. Backyards should be very firmly secured and they should have supervison at all times. Squirt prefers to stay close and has not shown and desire to escape. They are both fully potty trained granted they received enough opportunities to use the washroom. They may have accidents after stressful experiences (like visits to the vet or changes in environment) so adopters should expect an adjustment period.

Squirt walks on leash very well but he does enjoy stopping to sniff or mark the ground. If Bailey pees somewhere, he has to go exactly where his brother did. Bailey is also a dream to walk on leash and will follow the pace of his humans. Sometimes if the lead is long enough he will walk ahead, but never pulls and will stop if his person stops.

Both are extremely well mannered in the home and don’t need much training. If they are not allowed on furniture they adapt quickly but do love to cuddle up next to their family. Both know sit and with high value treats have proven to be very trainable. They sleep in a dog bed together in their foster parents bedroom.

Squirt & Bailey are adaptable and can thrive in most living environments. Despite their age they love their walks and will need a family capable of providing 1-2 walks a day. They would prefer if their family is home more often than not, and will include them in daily activities. They have been tested with other small dogs and seem to do fine with everyone they meet. They have not been tested with cats.

If you’re interested in adopting Squirt & Bailey please apply at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/adoption-info#adoption-form

Squirt & Bailey’s adoption fee is $600. To learn more about our adoption fees and the adoption process, please visit our FAQs at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/about-us#about-faqs.

He absolutely has typical traits of both breeds as he is friendly, loves people and other dogs, smart, energetic, and happy! A home and family that is able to harness that energy and utilize his smarts would be the best case scenario for this young man. Clyde loves car rides, playing fetch and learning new tricks. He would make an awesome running, hiking and biking partner. He loves children but may be too big and boisterous for young children. His previous family loved him, but were an older couple and didn't have the time or energy to work with him. Because they want the best possible outcome for Clyde, he comes with an offer to pay for training with a professional dog trainer. Clyde is in a foster home in Missoula. His adoption fee is 150.00 and he is up to date on vaccinations. To meet Clyde please fill out an online application form on our website LSAR.org.
